00:25:45,173 --> 00:25:47,796
Both processes can actually happen in parallel.

194
00:25:48,636 --> 00:25:50,400
That's great and encouraging to hear.

195
00:25:51,300 --> 00:25:55,646
Of course, thinking about it, the two are like positive and negative images.

196
00:25:55,886 --> 00:26:00,532
By developing the perfections, I can start reducing the taints and vice versa.

197
00:26:04,900 --> 00:26:07,605
Yeah, that's a lovely conclusion for us.

198
00:26:11,955 --> 00:26:24,343
I think that's a really good point that, you know, it manifests our diversity, all these different views, but also our fundamental unity, which he later points out.

199
00:26:24,998 --> 00:26:48,489
This image of the elephant, that's an old Indian image about, an old Indian simile about blind men feeling an elephant and then saying, well, saying that it's a brush, the tail, or it's a stump of a tree, the leg, completely misunderstanding the elephant as a total.

200
00:26:48,970 --> 00:26:54,616
And that's what happens when we cling to a view or an opinion and we think that we've got it all.

201
00:26:55,930 --> 00:27:05,219
It's a case of seeing our views and opinions, as he said, as a perspective.

202
00:27:11,724 --> 00:27:17,871
This business of working with the taints when they come up, but also developing the power of me.

203
00:27:18,751 --> 00:27:22,596
Yes, indeed, that's what we're instructed to do.

204
00:27:23,098 --> 00:27:31,238
And remember that the energy or the malevolent energy or the turbulences that come with the defilements, that energy is not lost.

205
00:27:31,617 --> 00:27:33,663
It is transformed.

206
00:27:34,484 --> 00:27:36,690
In fact, the word I prefer is sublimate.

207
00:27:37,432 --> 00:27:42,001
It moves directly from the...

208
00:27:42,353 --> 00:28:04,497
the unwholesome state directly into the wholesome and sometimes you might actually experience that I remember I was having a hard time with my teacher once and I was on doing a personal retreat and I was working with this real deep disappointment I had in him and it came up with a lot of aversion

209
00:28:05,319 --> 00:28:11,946
And being a very good meditator at that time, I just stayed with the feeling, stayed with the feeling.

210
00:28:12,448 --> 00:28:24,161
And to my real honest surprise, it just turned in front of me into this really warm, compassionate feeling for him.

211
00:28:24,942 --> 00:28:32,609
And that manifested for me that these energies, they just turn.

212
00:28:33,028 --> 00:28:35,452
they evaporate and become something else.

213
00:28:36,694 --> 00:28:39,259
So you can work on both.

214
00:28:49,777 --> 00:28:53,063
Yes, on that last line, the bit about...

215
00:28:55,372 --> 00:28:58,516
hopefully lead to a better collective and individual actions of the world.

216
00:28:59,256 --> 00:29:15,976
I was told a story by Nori, she was in Bulgaria, and somebody told her that he was in Sofia, the capital, and just noticed that lots of people were walking towards the center.

217
00:29:16,856 --> 00:29:18,538
And so he joined in.

218
00:29:19,318 --> 00:29:23,403
And a whole crowd began to develop in the central square.

219
00:29:24,278 --> 00:29:36,335
And then one man got up and began to talk about all the people, all his relatives or friends who'd gone missing in the communist era and stuff like that.

220
00:29:36,934 --> 00:29:40,619
And more and more people got up to talk about their grievances.

221
00:29:41,682 --> 00:29:46,709
And the building, the government building behind them was full of lights, it seems.

222
00:29:47,589 --> 00:29:53,458
And eventually, when everything had been spoken, seemingly everybody turned

223
00:29:53,692 --> 00:29:56,755
and looked into the building and all the lights started to go out.

224
00:29:59,037 --> 00:30:01,118
And there's a presumption that they were all escaping.

225
00:30:01,799 --> 00:30:07,464
And from that moment onwards, it seems the communist government began to give in.

226
00:30:08,286 --> 00:30:11,949
And of course, that was all around 89 when the wall collapsed.

227
00:30:13,170 --> 00:30:23,259
And looking back at that time, generally speaking, what a peaceful revolution that was, you know.

228
00:30:24,234 --> 00:30:34,550
you know, comparing to the earlier times when there were uprisings in Hungary, 56, I think, which were brutally suppressed, you know.

229
00:30:35,992 --> 00:30:43,324
So the whole purpose of us really, you know, considering these different

230
00:30:43,574 --> 00:30:58,308
qualities is to really begin to see how they can manifest through our economics and our social life even personally individually it might

231
00:30:58,676 --> 00:31:21,613
make us much more aware of what we're buying, what we're eating, etc., etc., and how we talk to others, how we actually begin to persuade others, especially those whom we meet who have opposite views and opinions, perhaps to get them to open up to our views and for us to understand theirs.

232
00:31:21,981 --> 00:31:32,876
I mean, we've been through this whole Brexit thing where it was very difficult for some people who were for staying to understand that anybody could want to leave, you know.

233
00:31:33,297 --> 00:31:35,380
And there's all this thing about them being a bit thick.

234
00:31:35,680 --> 00:31:39,685
They didn't understand.

235
00:31:39,705 --> 00:31:47,355
And, of course, it was one of the fundamental reasons that people wanted to leave was that they just weren't benefiting.

236
00:31:47,616 --> 00:31:50,200
They saw nothing but...

237
00:31:50,602 --> 00:32:05,124
their own poverty and the immigration had made them feel a loss of, this is the white, the English people and the Welsh had made them, their sense of community was being undermined.

238
00:32:08,327 --> 00:32:11,393
Anyway, that's what we have to do.

239
00:32:11,452 --> 00:32:16,760
We have to keep these values, these virtues in our minds and

240
00:32:17,332 --> 00:32:22,838
whenever the opportunity comes to say what's necessary, to be open about it, not to be afraid.

241
00:32:24,101 --> 00:32:29,928
And hopefully we shall move towards a very wonderful and enlightened society in no length of time.

242
00:32:31,029 --> 00:32:31,450
We can hope.

243
00:32:32,592 --> 00:32:37,617
So with those wonderful words, let us now begin our practice.

